<anchor xml:id="_group__G05_1ga2275869d5ec1bd0eaea2e278e2a70cc7"/><section>
    <title>formatFrequency()</title>
<indexterm><primary>formatFrequency</primary><secondary>Tools method</secondary></indexterm>
<indexterm><primary>Tools method</primary><secondary>formatFrequency</secondary></indexterm>
<para><computeroutput>char * RDA5807::formatFrequency (uint16_t value, char * strValue, char decimalSeparator)<computeroutput>[inline]</computeroutput></computeroutput></para><para>

<para>Convert a numeric frequency to a formated string (char *) frequency. </para>
</para>

<para>
                <formalpara>
                    <title>
Parameters</title>
                    <para>
                    <table frame="all">
                        <tgroup cols="2" align="left" colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                        <colspec colwidth="1*"/>
                        <colspec colwidth="4*"/>
                        <tbody>
                            <row>
<entry>uint16_t</entry><entry>
<para>value - Frequency to be formated </para>
</entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
<entry>char</entry><entry>
<para>*strValue - Formated frequency (Exe: 103,90) - Array of char ( minimal 7 elements ) </para>
</entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
<entry>char</entry><entry>
<para>decimalSeparator - the symbol that separates the decimal part (Exe: . or ,) </para>
</entry>
                            </row>
                        </tbody>
                        </tgroup>
                    </table>
                    </para>
                </formalpara>
                <formalpara><title>Returns</title>

